Citation.sAbstract: The gaseous PVT properties of ethyl fluoride (HFC-161) were measured at temperatures from 300.16 to 370.15K and corresponding pressures from 0.6422 to 3.9562MPa using the isochoric method. The maximum uncertainties were estimated to be within +-1.5 kPa for pressure and within +-6mK for temperature. The purity of the HFC-161 sample used in the present measurements was 99.74 wt%. A virial-type equation of state was developed based on the present measurements; this equation reproduced the experimental data in the gas phase within +-0.28% in pressure and within +-0.38% in density. On the basis of the present PVT properties and vapor pressures measured, saturated vapor densities of HFC-161 were determined, and a correlation of saturated vapor densities was presented.
Citation.sTitle: Gaseous PVT properties of ethyl fluoride
